Quick, Simple & Easy, Creamy Chicken Garlic Pasta! Bookmark THIS RECIPE! Like and Follow @deynsrecipies for more great recipes! Ingredients: Creamy, dreamy, and oh-so-delicious - this garlic chicken pasta recipe is one you won't want to miss! 1 lb of boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into bite sized pieces marinated with the following: • 1 tbsp spicy chicken seasoning • 1/2 tsp garlic salt •1/2 tsp black pepper • 1lb linguine, salted and cooked al Dante • 3 tbsp olive oil • 3 cloves garlic, minced • One hand full of baby spinach, washed and drained • 4 tbsp butter • 2 tbsp all purpose flour Salt and pepper to taste • 1/2 tsp red chili flakes • 1/2 tsp parsley • 1/2 tsp oregano • 1/2 cup milk •1 cup heavy cream •1 cup grated mozzarella cheese Add the oil to a pan, on medium-high heat and fry the chicken for high heat and fry the chicken for . 2-3 minutes Cook until the chicken is browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the chicken and set aside. To the same pan, add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds. Add the spinach, once it's wilted - move it to one side. Add the butter roux. Add seasonings followed by the milk, stirring continuously. Add the cream and stir until it thickens then add the spinach and chicken. Add the pasta, followed by the chicken and cheese and mix to combine. Serve the creamy garlic chicken pasta hot, garnished with fresh parsley and basil.
